INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (62,1,'2013-10-09 21:12:01','2013-10-09 21:12:01','“Red light cameras” are becoming a common traffic enforcement tool. More and more traffic cameras are being implemented as municipalities learn the fines produce a pretty reliable income stream.  Unfortunately, this means you may, if you have not already, receive a picture of your smiling mug coasting through an intersection, along with a citation for a moving violation.\r\n\r\nDo not fret.  There is a light at the end of the tunnel.  Across the country, people are successfully defeating these citations.\r\n\r\nThe Federal Highway Administration, a branch of the Department of Transportation, publishes a signal timing manual (yes one of these exists).  The manual includes recommended yellow light times based on the posted speed limit of the intersection.  The manual can be found in pdf format at: <a href=\"http://ops.fhwa.dot.gov/publications/fhwahop08024/fhwa_hop_08_024.pdf\">http://ops.fhwa.dot.gov/publications/fhwahop08024/fhwa_hop_08_024.pdf</a>.<!--more-->\r\n\r\nIf you are ticketed for going through a red light, go back to that intersection and time the yellow.  If it is less than 3 seconds (in  a 25 mph zone), less than 3.2 in a 30 mph, etc., you have grounds to fight the citation as the light is probably not up to code.  Bring the Signal Timing Manual into traffic court and say something like: “Most importantly, this light is dangerous.  The light does not even meet the <i>minimum </i>requirement according to the federal regulations.  The short yellow will result in people slamming on their brakes or speeding through the intersection causing otherwise safe drivers to become unsafe.  Second, with a duration much less than the recommended time, it is almost impossible to stop before the red.”\r\n\r\nSo if you are “caught on camera” going through a red light, you can do one of two things.  1. You can get the amount of money required to pay the fine, put it on a table, and take a photograph to send back with the picture of you going through the red light (this is NOT RECOMMENDED), or 2. Time the yellow at the intersection.  If you time the yellow and it is less than the recommendation, you have a defense.','\"It Was Yellow!\"','','publish','closed','open','','it-was-yellow','','','2013-10-09 21:33:18','2013-10-09 21:33:18','',0,'http://myvaccinelawyer.com/blog/?p=62',0,'post','',0);
